  "prompt": "How many questions are asked on Quora each minute on average?",
  "response": "As of the latest available data up to 2023, Quora does not provide a specific figure for the number of questions asked per minute on its platform. However, it has been reported that Quora receives tens of thousands of questions daily. To estimate the number of questions asked per minute, we can make an approximation based on these reports.\n\nIf Quora receives 20,000 questions per day, for example:\n- There are 24 hours in a day.\n- Each hour has 60 minutes.\n\nSo, you can approximate as follows:\n- 20,000 questions/day \u00f7 (24 hours/day \u00d7 60 minutes/hour) = 20,000 \u00f7 1,440 \u2248 13.89 questions/minute.\n\nBased on this method, an estimate would suggest roughly 14 questions per minute on average. Note that this is a rough approximation and the actual number may vary.",
